<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. POLICY ON CAMBODIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Administration's recent about-face on Cambodia can only be applauded, no 
matter how late the reversal comes, and no matter the degree of previous 
support for a despicable policy. That this, and previous, Administrations have 
helped to fund a group of rebel forces that includes the Khmer Rouge must rank 
as one of the venal acts in U.S foreign-policy history. 
</P>
<P>
REILLY POLLARD 
</P>
<P>
Goleta 
</P>
