<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORIOLES GET KITTLE IN DEAL FOR BRADLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Baltimore Orioles traded outfielder Phil Bradley to the Chicago White Sox 
for first baseman Ron Kittle, Oriole spokesman Bob Miller said late Sunday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley, a 31-year-old right-handed hitting outfielder, is in the last year of 
his contract with the Orioles and was eligible for free agency at the end of 
the season. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley, hitting .270 with four home runs and 26 RBIs, had expressed 
displeasure at the course of recent contract talks. 
</P>
<P>
Miller said both players are expected to report to their respective new teams 
in time for tonight's games. 
