<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL OKS GRANTS TO 4 SOCIAL AGENCIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved $21,900 in grants for four social service 
agencies in South County. 
</P>
<P>
San Juan Capistrano's South County Community Clinic will get $10,000, the 
largest amount. 
</P>
<P>
The Sober Living Center, an alcohol rehabilitation program with three locations 
in Dana Point, will receive $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
Casa del Cerro, a substance-abuse counseling service in Dana Point, will 
receive $3,300, and $3,600 will go to the South Orange County Community 
Services Council, which has offices in San Clemente and Mission Viejo and makes 
referrals to social service agencies. 
</P>
<P>
The grants were awarded out of a total of eight applicants requesting $61,539. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council has budgeted $50,000 this year for human services groups. The 
remainder of the money will be awarded in September. LEN HALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
