<P>
TEENS KILL GRANDMA ON BIRTHDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHARLEROI, Belgium 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Belgian teen-agers murdered their grandmother on her birthday -- but it 
took them several attempts to do so, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
They first gave Solange Deval a present of chocolate eclairs laced with Valium, 
but she did not die. 
</P>
<P>
They then forced the 62-year-old woman to inhale tear gas from a small canister 
used by women to fend off attackers. But again she did not die. 
</P>
<P>
They finally killed her when they knocked her out with chloroform, beat her 
with a broom handle and strangled her, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Gravedigger Frans Mahau, the father of the pair, had confessed under 
questioning to plotting with his children to murder Deval at her home in the 
southern town of Charleroi on July 21, the spokesman said. "This was a family 
plot of the most macabre kind," he added. 
</P>
