<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Richard Widmark was in satisfactory condition at New Milford Hospital 
Monday, recovering from leg injuries suffered in a weekend lawn-mower accident, 
a hospital spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Widmark, 75, was taken to the hospital by ambulance about 6 p.m. Sunday and 
underwent surgery on his lower left leg and foot, said Hank Fanberg, a hospital 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Fanberg did not know the extent of injuries or other details of the accident. 
</P>
<P>
"He picked a fight with his lawn mower," Fanberg said. 
</P>
<P>
Widmark has owned a home in Roxbury for years. 
</P>
<P>
His more recent screen credits include "Murder on the Orient Express," "The 
Swarm," and "Against All Odds." 
</P>
<P>
Widmark starred in the television series "Madigan" in 1972, as the character he 
portrayed in the 1968 film of the same name. 
